# AGENTS.local.md (template)

**User- and environment-specific** settings for *this* checkout by *this* user. Family-level data (children, household, homes, tone, sensitive topics, family vocabulary) lives in `AGENTS.family.md`.

Different family members and different machines can maintain different `AGENTS.local.md` files. This one should not be shared across users.

> ⚠️ This file, once instantiated, can still reveal that *this repo* contains personal family content. The scaffold assumes your entire repo is private — see `PRIVACY.md`. If your repo is public, stop and fix that before filling this out.

**Note:** the renamed `AGENTS.local.md` is gitignored. Your preferences stay on your machine and won't be committed.

Rename this file to `AGENTS.local.md` (no `.example`) and fill it in. Your agent reads the full layer chain at the start of every session: `AGENTS.md` (core), `AGENTS.overlay.md` (if present), `AGENTS.family.md`, then `AGENTS.local.md`.

---

## Privacy state

```yaml
privacy_acknowledged: false         # set to true once you've read PRIVACY.md and confirmed your setup
privacy_warning_dismissed: false    # set to true after agent removes the dismissable warning block from AGENTS.md
acknowledged_on: null               # YYYY-MM-DD
```

## Agent preferences

Per-user / per-environment preferences for how the agent operates in this checkout.

```yaml
preferences:
  capture_prompt_interval_days: 14
  lint_prompt_interval_days: 30
  auto_update_timeline: true
  auto_update_profile_shared_experiences: true
  explain_placement_choices: true
  auto_commit: false                # set true to let the agent commit its own changes without asking each time
  auto_push: false                  # set true to let the agent push to the remote after committing
```

**Default (both flags `false`):** the agent stages changes and shows you a diff, but waits for your approval before running `git commit` or `git push`. Flip either flag to `true` if you trust the agent to complete the git operation on its own.

**Fail-closed:** these flags are **only** permissive when they are **explicitly present and set to `true`**. If this file doesn't exist, or if a flag is absent / commented out / set to anything other than `true`, the agent must treat it as `false` and ask before committing or pushing. An absent key is not consent. Don't rely on a verbal "yeah go ahead and auto-commit from now on" — either flip the flag here, or approve each operation as it happens.

**Both flags gated on privacy.** Both `auto_commit` and `auto_push` require `privacy_acknowledged: true` above. Even with `auto_push: true`, the agent will refuse to push to a public remote.

In Claude Code, a PreToolUse hook (`.claude/hooks/pre-git-guard.sh`) enforces these rules at the shell layer — it blocks `git commit` and `git push` invocations that aren't sanctioned by the flags. Other harnesses rely on the agent following the prose rule in `AGENTS.md`.

## Personal tone overrides

Anything specific to *you* that should override the family default `tone` declared in `AGENTS.md`. Leave blank to inherit.

```yaml
tone_override:
  register: ""                      # "warm", "clinical", "terse", "playful", "literary" — or leave "" to inherit
  pov: ""                           # "parent", "neutral third-person", "journal-style" — or leave "" to inherit
  avoid_words: []                   # your personal additions; merged with family list
```

## Notes for the agent

Free-form space for anything else this user wants the agent to know about working with this checkout (e.g. "I ingest on Sundays", "don't auto-push when on mobile hotspot", etc.).

